# Definition of Done — <feature / change name>

A scoped DoD lives alongside a plan. It's the explicit checklist the team uses to call work "done"
for *this* change. It is not a generic template — fill it in.

## Functional

- [ ] All planned iterations landed.
- [ ] Acceptance criteria from each iteration met.
- [ ] Manual verification of golden path completed.
- [ ] Edge cases identified during planning are exercised.

## Tests

- [ ] Unit tests added/updated for changed logic.
- [ ] Integration tests cover the new seam(s).
- [ ] E2E updated if a user-visible journey changed.
- [ ] CI is green on the branch.
- [ ] No skipped/quarantined tests added in this change.

## Code review

- [ ] `/review` run; no unresolved Blockers or Majors.
- [ ] `security-reviewer` consulted if §10 of the plan flagged it.
- [ ] `architecture-reviewer` consulted if a new contract / module / service was introduced.

## Security

- [ ] OWASP categories from §10 addressed in code (not deferred).
- [ ] Secrets handled via the project's secret manager (not committed, not logged).
- [ ] AuthN/AuthZ checks present at every new ingress.
- [ ] Input validation at trust boundaries.
- [ ] No new sinks reachable from untrusted input without explicit mitigation.

## Observability

- [ ] Logs from §11 emit on the relevant paths.
- [ ] Metrics from §11 registered; no high-cardinality labels.
- [ ] Traces propagated across any new RPC/queue hops.
- [ ] Alerts (if any) have runbooks linked.

## Rollout

- [ ] Feature flag (if any) defaults to safe value.
- [ ] Deploy plan from §12 followed.
- [ ] Success metric green for <stated window>.
- [ ] Rollback path verified (at least dry-runnable).

## Documentation

- [ ] User-facing docs updated where behavior changed.
- [ ] Internal architecture docs updated where structure changed.
- [ ] ADR written if a structural decision was made.

## Hygiene

- [ ] No leftover `TODO(claude)` / `FIXME(claude)` without a follow-up issue.
- [ ] No commented-out code, debug prints, or scratch files in the diff.
- [ ] Follow-ups filed (linked below).

